<p>I have <code>wait</code> in my tests like this:</p>  <pre><code>WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(dr, TimeSpan.FromSeconds(30));  ...  wait.Until((d) =&gt; {    if (d.FindElement(By.XPath("//*[@src='/loader.gif']")).Displayed)    {        System.Threading.Thread.Sleep(200);        return false;    }    else    {        return true;    } }); </code></pre>  <p>I sometimes get <code>StaleElementReferenceException</code>. It works 95% of time and its failing on different places in test.</p>  <p>Error:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Message: OpenQA.Selenium.StaleElementReferenceException : Element not   found in the cache - perhaps the page has changed since it was looked   up</p> </blockquote>